From dafcd073afdd68083a5b17c96a46b3a946eb51f2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Lids Labs <55252374+lidslabs@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 14:27:39 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 15/18] lidslabs v0.4.0: transcoder splash for HLS transcode
 starts (LIDSLABS_TRANSCODE_SPLASH)

Masks the ~5-6s transcode-start dead window (black screen, no buffering UI on
most clients) by prepending pre-encoded splash segments to the server-generated
HLS variant playlist, separated from the real content by #EXT-X-DISCONTINUITY.
Three hooks, all in this controller:

- GetVariantPlaylistInternal: splice cached splash segments into the playlist
  and fire a warm start of the real transcode so the encoder ramp overlaps
  splash playback (state ownership transfers to the warm task).
- GetDynamicSegment: adopt an in-flight warm job for init/segment-0 requests
  instead of killing and restarting it (disk-based currentTranscodingIndex is
  null while the warm job is still ramping).
- New route Videos/{itemId}/hls1/splash/{segmentId}.{container} serving
  splash segments statically from a per-profile rendition cache under
  <cache>/lidslabs-splash/, generated on first use via jellyfin-ffmpeg.

Renditions match the session's segment container, video codec, audio codec and
dynamic range (SDR/PQ/HLG via zscale for HDR-passthrough sessions) because
libavformat-based players keep one decoder across a discontinuity - verified
against jellyfin-ffmpeg 7.1.4: mpegts with matched codecs splices cleanly;
an fMP4 EXT-X-MAP switch is skipped by libavformat (AVPlayer/hls.js handle it).

Off by default: with LIDSLABS_TRANSCODE_SPLASH unset every hook short-circuits
and the playlist bytes are unchanged. All splash failure paths (missing source,
unsupported profile, rendition not yet generated, generation/warm-start errors)
fall through to stock playback.
